  [1] A nuance here is that the big exchange operators tend to run multiple=
 venues, and if you are starting a second exchange your goal is probably no=
t to displace the first: Your goal is to offer some different trading mecha=
nics or fee structure or listing standards, so that your trading or listing=
 customers can get an optimized experience.


  [2] I am guessing at that one. But TXSE=E2=80=99s press release emphasize=
s that it =E2=80=9Cwill provide a venue to trade and list public companies =
and the growing universe of exchange-traded products,=E2=80=9D so it is com=
peting for ETP listings, and BlackRock is an investor. It would make sense =
for a smallish exchange with no volume to compete for ETF listings on price=
.


