</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Naively, you might think that a stock =
exchange is a place where people meet to trade stocks, and that everyone wo=
uld want to meet where everyone else meets. If everybody is trading stocks =
under one particular <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvQnV0dG9ud29vZF9B=
Z3JlZW1lbnQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB013e540a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">buttonwood tree</a> =
in lower Manhattan, and you would prefer to trade stocks under an elm tree =
in midtown, you can go to some other traders and say =E2=80=9Chey isn=E2=80=
=99t this elm tree nice and shady, let=E2=80=99s trade there,=E2=80=9D but =
it will be hard to get any of them to move. They have stock to sell, and th=
ey want to sell it where the buyers are; they have stock to buy, and they w=
ant to buy it where the sellers are. Even if your elm tree offers better sh=
ade and lower fees, they=E2=80=99ll be inclined to stick with the buttonwoo=
d. Liquidity begets liquidity, and it is hard for a small upstart exchange =
to compete with the incumbents.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the act=
ual US equity market in 2024 doesn=E2=80=99t really work like that. There a=
re more than a dozen <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9mYXN0LWFuc3dlcnMvZGl2aXNpb25z=
bWFya2V0cmVnbXJleGNoYW5nZXNzaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe1a0a24c" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">stock exchanges</a>, plus various other trading venues, and all of them =
are actually computers. So if you are a stock trader, your calculation is n=
ot =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m going to walk over to one particular place and stan=
d there trading stocks all day, so it=E2=80=99d better be the place with th=
e most people.=E2=80=9D Your calculation is more like =E2=80=9CI am going t=
o connect my computer to 37 other computers, all of which will sell me stoc=
k, and trade on all of them simultaneously.=E2=80=9D The default approach i=
s to connect to many different trading venues and send each order to whiche=
ver venue has the best price at any particular second.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">And this is not just a matter of convenient computer tech=
nology; it is also fostered by US regulation. The US has a =E2=80=9C<a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cubmFzZGFxLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9yZWctbm1zLWR1bW1pZXMtMjAxOS0wNS0wOQ/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB69c7e862" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">national market system</a>=E2=80=9D t=
hat links together all of the exchanges and that=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmN=
vcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0Mi42MTE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd69b3a21"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">more or less=C2=A0requires</a> brokers to do a trade on whichever =
exchange offers the best price. So if you have an upstart stock exchange, a=
nd it is approved by the US Securities and Exchange Commission to be a =E2=
=80=9Cnational securities exchange,=E2=80=9D all the traders will connect t=
o your exchange, and if you have the best price for one stock at 10:17 on W=
ednesday morning, the trade will happen on your exchange. In the naive simp=
le meet-under-the-tree system, offering a little bit of liquidity is no goo=
d: Everyone will prefer to meet at the place that offers a lot of liquidity=
. In the national market system, you can run a perfectly viable business of=
fering a little bit of liquidity.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Probably =
that=E2=80=99s not anyone=E2=80=99s goal. Probably most people who want=C2=
=A0to start exchanges think=C2=A0that their exchange idea is the best one=
=C2=A0and that it will in time become a big player and displace the big inc=
umbents, the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq.<a class=3D"footnote-index"=
 href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display:=
 inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But the point is that you=C2=A0<em>can=C2=A0</em>start small and =
try to grow, so a lot of people give it a go. We are in a bit of a golden a=
ge of stock-exchange experimentation.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Becau=
se if you=E2=80=99re starting an exchange, you probably do need some value =
proposition beyond =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re a computer where you can trade st=
ocks.=E2=80=9D You need a story to attract investors and attention and ulti=
mately traders. So we have talked=C2=A0about <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTUtMTItMjIvdGhlLWZsYXNoLWJveXMtZXhjaGFuZ2UtaXM=
tc3RpbGwtY29udHJvdmVyc2lhbD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjA1MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaX=
VtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA2MDUmdXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB33b1937c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">IEX</a>, the =
Investors=E2=80=99 Exchange, whose initial proposition was something like =
=E2=80=9Cwe will protect long-term investors from evil high-frequency trade=
rs, and Michael Lewis <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d25vcnRvbi5jb20vYm9va3MvZmxhc2gtYm95cy8/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBeda72543" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">wrote a book</a> about us.=E2=80=9D=
 We have talked about <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS92aWV3L2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMTctMTAtMTYvdGhlLWxvbmctdGVybS1zdG9jay1leGNoYW5nZS1pcy13b3J0aC1hLXNob3Q_Y2=
1waWQ9QkJEMDYwNTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld=
3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNjA1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cBa28329e7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">LTSE</a>, the Long-Term Stock Exchange, who=
se proposition was something like =E2=80=9Cwe will protect public-company c=
hief executive officers from the short-term demands of public investors.=E2=
=80=9D We have talked about <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fyd=
