r-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; =
display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a> If you want your stock to trade publicly, you list it on an exchange (=
mainly NYSE or Nasdaq). Your stock=C2=A0<em>trades=C2=A0</em>on every excha=
nge =E2=80=94=C2=A0it's a national market system, everyone can buy and sell=
 every stock everywhere =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it is=C2=A0<em>listed=C2=A0</em>=
on one of them. You pay fees to your listing exchange, the listing exchange=
 has an outsized role in trading the stock (doing the <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
