=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
delisted from the Nasdaq</a>=C2=A0and stopped trading. It makes sense that =
the company would not be worth much: It was a bet on a biopharmaceutical id=
ea, and it didn=E2=80=99t work out.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the =
other hand, NeuBase isn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>worthless</em>. It has a bunch o=
f cash and no real debt, and it gave up on its plans before it ran out of m=
oney. There=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>much money left; in April=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35613642.264315/a=
