NjU5MjQwNjA1NjgvdG0yNDE0MjgzZDFfOGsuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC362ac2c4"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">got about 1.25 million shares</a> to vote in favor of dissolution.=
 About 94% of the shares that voted were in favor, but that comes to only a=
bout 33% of the total shares outstanding, so it=E2=80=99s not enough to dis=
solve the company. It tried again on May 22 and <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35613642.264315/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9pe=
